HEADWORD: Persalt
<hw>Per"salt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A term formerly given to the salts supposed to be formed respectively by neutralizing acids with certain peroxides.</def> <mark>[Obsoles.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

